        "file_name": "05_virtue_focus.md",
        "content": "### Virtue Focus: Patience\n\nPatience is a key virtue in learning Latin, as it requires time and effort to master new concepts. As students work through the first declension nouns, they are encouraged to be patient with themselves and their peers. James 1:4 reminds us, 'Let perseverance finish its work so that you may be mature and complete, not lacking anything.' This week, students will reflect on how patience aids in their understanding and retention of Latin grammar."
